      "id": 1,
      "text": "Incorporated in 1903, Crystal River proudly calls itself the 'Home of the Manatee'.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crystal_River%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Kings Bay’s spring‑fed waters stay a steady 72°F, drawing more than 400 manatees each winter.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15,
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crystal_River%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The city’s springs form a first‑magnitude system that discharges about 64 million gallons a day, making it Florida’s second‑largest spring group.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16,
        17,
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crystal_River%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1888 the railroad reached Crystal River, opening the town to easier shipping and trade.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
